---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About Ilyas Alhassan — Data Scientist and AI Engineer." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<article>
				<h1>About</h1>

				<p class="lede">
					I ship AI systems for a living. I write about the gap between the
					demo and the deploy.
				</p>

				<h2>What I work on</h2>
				<p>
					I'm a Data Scientist and AI Engineer at Bio-Techne, where I lead
					GenAI initiatives across the company. I've shipped a multi-agent
					sales intelligence platform serving hundreds of weekly users, a
					production technical-support assistant retrieving over a million
					Salesforce records, document intelligence pipelines that process PDFs
					at scale, and decision agents that have to answer correctly the
					first time because there isn't a second chance.
				</p>
				<p>
					Before GenAI was a category, I built classical machine learning
					systems — recommendation engines, predictive pipelines, anomaly
					detection — and ML pipelines for protein engineering that
					commercialized AI-designed therapeutics. The tools change every six
					months. The hard parts don't.
				</p>

				<h2>What I write about</h2>
				<p>
					Most public writing about AI right now is either hype or theory.
					There's a shortage of writing from the people actually shipping
					these systems into regulated, high-stakes environments where "the
					model hallucinated" is an incident, not a tweet.
				</p>
				<p>
					This site is my contribution to closing that gap. Specifics over
					generalities. Scars over claims. The things I wish someone had
					written before I had to figure them out the hard way.
				</p>
				<p>
					Topics I keep returning to: grounded retrieval, evaluation that
					survives reality, agent architecture, production failure modes, and
					the long unglamorous middle between a demo and a system you can run
					at three in the morning when something breaks.
				</p>

				<h2>Get in touch</h2>
				<p>
					Email: <a href="mailto:hello@ilyashassan.dev">hello@ilyashassan.dev</a><br />
					LinkedIn: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ilyasalhassan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">/in/ilyasalhassan</a><br />
					GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/ilyas-hassan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@ilyas-hassan</a>
				</p>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	main {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 3rem 1rem;
	}
	article h1 {
		font-size: 2.25rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		line-height: 1.1;
	}
	article h2 {
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		margin-top: 2.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}
	.lede {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	article p {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.75;
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	}
	article a {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}
</style>